The paper deals with computational problems related to gerrymandering and reverse gerrymandering, which are topics in computational social choice (cs.SI) and game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves partitioning voters into districts, which can be modeled using graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms for solving the problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
